criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. PD diagnosis from the United Kingdom Research Brain Bank diagnostic criteria for PD
             (Hughes et al., 1992);

          2. PD-MCI diagnosis from the Movement Disorder Society Task Force diagnostic criteria.
             Single and multiple-domain MCI were both included, only if executive functions were
             significantly impaired (-1 standard deviation on executive function tests according to
             age and education-adjusted norms);

          3. Montreal Cognitive Assessment scores between 21 and 27;

          4. Anti-Parkinson medication stable (at screening) since at least two months;

          5. All other medications, including psychotropics, stable for at least three months.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Participants with PD and dementia diagnosis

          2. Patients with other neurological or psychiatric disorders.
